headline.main: JAPANESE AIR RAID BROKEN UP BY R.A.F.; 13 of 22 Planes Damaged in Attack Over Bengal

lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI, India, March 31 (U.P.) -- Royal Air Force fliers intercepted twenty-two Japanese bombers and fighters attacking a British forward landing ground in Southeastern Bengal, India, and damaged thirteen, five of them severely, a British communique reported today.
abstract: India raids: RAF damages 13 of 22 Jap bombers raiding Brit landing ground, southeastern Bengal; Axis radio repts 6 Brit planes destroyed by Jap fliers, Chittagong area
